      Funding secured!
   =20
 =20
We=E2=80=99re  still doing this huh:Elon Musk says his 2018 tweet about pla=
nning to take Tesla Inc. private was =E2=80=9Centirely truthful=E2=80=9D an=
d that investors who claim the missive was fraudulent are wrong.Lawyers for=
 the billionaire chief executive officer of the electric-car maker said in =
a court filing Tuesday that Saudi Arabia=E2=80=99s sovereign wealth fund ha=
d indeed agreed to support his attempt to take the company private.=E2=80=
=9CElon Musk=E2=80=99s August 7, 2018 tweet informing the public that he wa=
s considering taking Tesla private was entirely truthful,=E2=80=9D the CEO=
=E2=80=99s attorney Alex Spiro said in a heavily redacted filing. =E2=80=9C=
Mr. Musk was considering taking Tesla private at $420 a share. Funding was =
secured. There was investor support.=E2=80=9DWhat is specifically going on =
here is that some investors sued Musk for securities fraud for that tweet, =
and they=C2=A0have asked a judge for partial summary judgment: They want th=
e judge to rule that the tweet was false, so that they can go to trial on q=
uestions of damages, etc. Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers filed a brief opposing tha=
t motion and demanding that a jury get to decide if the tweet was false. Th=
at seems reasonable.The actual evidence that Musk had lined up $70 billion =
of committed financing to take Tesla private is redacted in the public vers=
ion of the brief and, uh, I don=E2=80=99t believe it? The U.S. Securities a=
nd Exchange Commission  went through all of this with Musk and Tesla back w=
hen it  fined him $20 million for that tweet, and Musk=E2=80=99s own public=
 blogging  made it pretty clear that (1) he never got committed funding fro=
m the Saudi fund and (2) he never even asked for=C2=A0sufficient funding to=
 actually take Tesla private.=C2=A0Instead he had some sort of half-baked n=
otion that he would =E2=80=9Ctake Tesla private=E2=80=9D without buying mos=
t of the shares: Tesla would be =E2=80=9Cprivate=E2=80=9D instead of =E2=80=
=9Cpublic,=E2=80=9D but have most of the same shareholders, so he would not=
 need much cash. This was a weird and implausible idea but he=E2=80=99s a w=
eird and implausible guy and if he wants to argue it again to a jury they s=
hould probably let him.
