      Play-to-earn
   =20
 =20
Sure! Sure!  Sure:Tinder is rolling out a virtual currency to encourage use=
rs to spend more time swiping, scrolling and eventually spending real money=
 on the most popular dating app in the U.S.Initially available only in Aust=
ralia, the in-app =E2=80=9Ccoins=E2=80=9D can be acquired as users remain a=
ctive on the platform or keep their profiles up to date. They can also be b=
ought with regular money. The coins can then be used to step up a user=E2=
=80=99s profile by purchasing Tinder=E2=80=99s perks such as Super Likes or=
 Boosts, which can help increase the chances of finding a good match. =E2=
=80=A6The in-app currency, which will be available later this month, is par=
t of Tinder=E2=80=99s efforts to create a richer experience for people onli=
ne, moving beyond just its traditional =E2=80=9Cswipe right=E2=80=9D method=
 for finding a romantic partner. Tinder, owned by Match Group Inc., expects=
 the virtual currency to enable more opportunities to earn money from the a=
pp. Chief Financial Officer Gary Swidler said during the company=E2=80=99s =
second-quarter earnings call that Tinder users=E2=80=99 =E2=80=9Cpropensity=
 to pay has improved significantly.=E2=80=9DThe company expects the coins =
=E2=80=9Cwill play an important role as the Tinder experience evolves and b=
ecomes more immersive, because virtual currency is useful in the context of=
 gifting digital goods,=E2=80=9D Swidler said in a statement to Bloomberg.I=
 am looking forward to next year when I will read stories about=C2=A0Tinder=
coin venture capitalists who stake penniless young daters who work 12-hour =
days updating their profiles and give 50% of their Tindercoin earnings to t=
he venture capitalists. When I will read stories about how=C2=A0you can use=
 your Tindercoins to buy non-fungible tokens in the metaverse (a cartoon dr=
awing of a hat that you can put on your Tinder profile), and about how nobo=
dy will date anyone who does not have the right sort of NFT hat on their pr=
ofile picture. When I will read stories about how young people are not gett=
ing married anymore because it would require them to stop updating their Ti=
nder profiles and give up all their sweet sweet Tindercoins, which are now =
the main store of value in society. When I will read stories about how youn=
g people=C2=A0are=C2=A0getting married but keep updating their Tinder profi=
les and earning Tindercoins, which they spend on =E2=80=A6=C2=A0staking pen=
niless young daters? Cartoon hats? I don=E2=80=99t know. It is so rarely th=
at you find yourself at the dawn of a whole new way of organizing human soc=
iety, except that now it is every day and it=E2=80=99s exhausting.
