n. 21, when Bitcoin prices opened above $40,000, meaning he could have boug=
ht something like 0.15 Bitcoins, though he actually apparently split his mo=
ney between Bitcoin and Ether.[3] We have talked about stock splits before =
around here, for  Tesla Inc. and=C2=A0 twice for  Apple Inc., but they were=
n=E2=80=99t that interesting then either.[4] Possibly this history is inacc=
urate.
