leverage because it deals in piles of money: It costs Starbucks roughly 10 =
times as much effort to make 10 times as many coffees, for which it earns r=
oughly=C2=A010 times as much money; it does not cost Goldman that much more=
 effort to do a $10 billion merger than=C2=A0a $1 billion merger, but the $=
10 billion merger does bring in much higher fees.=C2=A0Still the money vari=
es in some rough proportion to the workload.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">There are =E2=80=A6=C2=A0other kinds of finance? Kinds that are less abou=
t providing client service? Certainly if you took your modest Goldman bonus=
