color: #ccc;"> so</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Alphabet=
 Inc. is bringing big stock splits back to the market, so prospective buyer=
s won=E2=80=99t need upwards of $3,000 to own a share. Taking down the pric=
e achieves something else for the Google parent: making it possible to put =
America=E2=80=99s third-biggest company into its most venerated stock avera=
ge.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company said late Tuesday it will i=
ncrease its outstanding shares by a 20-to-1 ratio, aiming to entice the num=
erous small investors who have flocked to the stock market during the pande=
mic. The shares jumped 10% in U.S. premarket trading on Wednesday, and were=
 set to surpass their record high reached last November.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe reason for the split is it makes our shares more=
 accessible,=E2=80=9D Ruth Porat, Alphabet=E2=80=99s chief financial office=
r, said in a conference call with television anchors. =E2=80=9CWe thought i=
t made sense to do.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For mom-and-po=
p traders, a lower stock price makes it easier to buy shares rather than pu=
rchase fractional stocks through their brokerage firms. Alphabet=E2=80=99s =
20-for-1 split would reduce the price of Class A shares to roughly $138, ba=
sed on Tuesday=E2=80=99s closing price of $2,752.88. A share of the company=
 hasn=E2=80=99t been that cheap since 2005.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>=E2=80=9CInstitutional investors can buy in size and the price per share d=
oesn=E2=80=99t matter,=E2=80=9D said Ed Clissold, chief U.S. strategist at =
Ned Davis Research. =E2=80=9CBut for a smaller investor, a lower price-per-=
share makes it easier for them to buy a reasonable number of shares.=E2=80=
=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">See I think that 0.05 shar=
es is a perfectly reasonable number of shares to buy in your Robinhood acco=
unt that encourages fractional-share investing,=C2=A0but no one agrees with=
 me and that=E2=80=99s fine.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think =
it=E2=80=99s charming that Alphabet cares? One very visible lesson of 2021 =
