rger sample of stocks, so the Dow does a decent job of tracking real indexe=
s like the S&amp;P 500; for another thing, most index-fund money is indexed=
 to real indexes so the Dow is probably not a huge driver of investment flo=
ws. Still it is a status symbol, and it drives some retail flows, and all t=
hat stuff is important right now so why not.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">Oh, by the way, an earlier version of that story said that =E2=80=9CAlpha=
